Visited this restaurant on Monday for the first time. We were seated promptly at our table outside. We were a party of three people we ordered drinks and food. After my second drink I needed to use the restroom. I put on my mask and entered inside the restaurant. The waiter stopped me abruptly and said “ You are not allowed to use  the bathroom because of the COVID-19.” I found this treatment rude because we spent over $200 on food and drinks and was never told prior to sitting that restrooms were not allowed. I have been to many restaurants during this time. As long as you are eating, drinking, and wear a mask bathrooms were always permitted.

Drinks are overpriced,  25$ for a mezcal served in a plastic cup ! You pay a bill of 280$ but are not allowed to Go to the bathroom and you will eat in carton plates paying for a fancy dinner. Even during covid, most restaurants are trying harder to better welcome their guests. Not recommended !

The ONLY reasons I gave this place a 3 star is because the cocktails were AMAZING! For the place to be simply decorated, it was still a nice intimate ambiance and the menu included food fare that was familiar, but with a twist. So instead of beef or pork ribs, they  have lamb ribs and instead of chicken tacos, they have mahi mahi tacos. Also, this restaurant holds it down for vegetarians and vegans alike. They have many options for the herbivores of NYC.  Now for the cons: I live in NYC where sometimes going out to eat is overpriced, but that's  because  they over feed you right??? Well here this is NOT the case; they bust you over the head for what you think is "dinner" and BOOM you get tapas! My boyfriend  and I were so confused. The menu definitely  says DINNER, but what you get isn't  dinner, you get a snack. Oh and clearly it's  something  that  is known by staff within the  restaurant because as my boyfriend is looking over the menu, the waitress states that maybe he should order two because the dishes aren't that big 🙄. At first, I thought she was throwing  shade at my honey because he's  chubby, but once we got our food I saw she wasn't  lying. As much as I enjoyed my cocktail, my tacos were soggy and falling  apart, not to mention the food was just ok and not filling at all.  So unless you want to get hustled out of  money by ordering multiple dinner plates that are the size of non-shareable tapas, you may want to explore other options. However, if you want to grab a drink or cocktail this is a nice cozy spot for that.

I live in the area and have always noticed a crowd around this place. My partner and I decided to stop by for an early dinner on a Saturday. Luckily their patio is dog friendly so I was able to dine with pup. We started off with the margarita and mezcalero from the drinks menu. There was a ton of salt on the rim of the margarita, and I preferred the mezcalero since it had a bit of citrus. For entrees, my partner ordered the steak tacos which had crispy cheese on the inside, very unusual, but very tasty. I ordered the octopus and pork belly, which was served on skewers with an avocado aioli. I didn't taste much avocado, but the octopus and pork belly skewer itself was well cooked and the poblano rice was also tasty. Honestly imo the best thing we ordered were the tater tots which came out super hot - crispy on the outside with mashed potato like filling Additionally my partner ordered a long island iced tea which was boozier than the other drinks, but pretty standard. Overall service was very good and attentive, prices for drinks are a bit high compared to the tapas plates, but this would be a great spot for happy hour if you don't want huge portions or are grabbing more food later.

Alright Google, let's talk about the most aesthetic bathroom I've ever seen. When you sit down, you're not surrounded by the usual cold, impersonal tiles, but instead by a warm, homey, wooden backdrop.  When the door closes behind you stop hearing the hustle and bustle of this popular eatery. Your ears are now caressed by Alta Calidads captivating alt/pop playlist, built to compliment this visually enticing bathroom.  Ladies and gentlemen, I wouldn't be raving about this bathroom were it not immaculatly clean. This, in addition to the warm air and cozy atmosphere, makes you feel like you're whizzing at home.  Next you'll notice the ceiling art. I won't spoil this lavish display for you but it's by far the most beautiful thing ive looked at while deucing.  As you go to wash your hands, you'll see, the most playful little candle wafting soft, summery scents that satisfy and satiate your every smoldering smidgen of sensory desire.  No doubt, for the duration of your bathroom journey you will continue to taste the savory entrees you enjoyed at your table. For those of you keeping count, this restaurant bathroom is a lush buffet for all five senses. An absolute must for any true conisseur.  20 out of 10, would poop again.

Loved it, but I recommend reservations.  Walked in during brunch on a cold winter morning  and managed to grab two spots at the bar, but just barely.  Thankfully, the food was worth the crowd, though, with the huevos rancheros offering a delightful remix of that hangover standby thanks to a light-as-a-cloud crispy potato cake and a red sauce my date and I immediately got obsessed with making at home.  I order papas bravas whenever I get the chance and Alta Calidad knocked it out of the park there, too, thanks to an enviably precise chop on the potatoes and a chipotle mayo that shames everyone else's flavorless attempts.

Hey management, get it together. I can’t believe the adamant refusal to accommodate. To preface, I did try to go slightly off menu. Tacos come in orders of two, but we were a party of three. I tried to order 3 tacos and our server told us the kitchen will not portion tacos that way. I found that hard to believe, so I kept asking. Our server said she would ask, and the manager came over.  Honestly the manager was 100% of the problem for the night. The service was otherwise great and the food was good. The manager told me that ordering off menu throws off the whole operation of the kitchen and that even him taking the time to talk to me was disruptive. I couldn’t believe he actually said that—customer service much? They made 0 accommodation for us—our tacos were orders of two and another dish that came later was accompanied by exactly 2 tortillas. Alta is great if you stay exactly on menu and are a party of two, but if you’re looking for even a modicum of hospitality, steer clear.

No. In fact, he was arrogant about the situation ("you know,  sometimes people stay longer than you plan"). Awful, right? But compare that flexible mindset to his inflexible refusal to give us a table that he'd previously reserved for someone else. MINDS BLOWN. I've eaten here many times and can say that the dinner menu is just as good as the brunch menu. You can't go wrong with anything on the menu, but the steak tacos and the lamb ribs are two of my favorites.  Cocktails are very well crafted as well.

I went with friends for late Sunday brunch. On the menu was a vegetarian Brussels sprouts enchilada I couldn't refuse. Limited seating, so I made a reservation in advance on Opentable. Sipped a delicious mezcal mule, as I finished those enchiladas alternating bites of potatas bravas and perfectly spiced black beans. Staff friendly and nice. Patrons awesome, too.  Can't wait to return to review dinner.
The food is delicious! Make sure that you make reservation in advance, there was a lineup outside!
Absolutely great Mexican food, awesome service and great cozy space! My margarita was not too bad either!
Really great casual spot with amazing staff and food. Drinks are fantastic. Indian influence on the Mexican menu is done incredibly well. Highly recommend!
I'm not fun of Mexican food at all, but I was pleasantly surprised, the food is straight delicious! Since the place is small I strongly recommend to make a reservation.
Great selection and wualoty of small plates. I also really liked the interior deaign and the atmosphere. This is not a typical mexican reataurant. Will definitely be back.
Delicious cocktails and food. Friendly staff. Cool, modern interior. Not crazy busy so you can get a seat on a Thursday night at 8pm.
If you are looking for reasonably priced and authentic Mexican cuisine DO it! This place is amazing great service, great atmosphere, and creative menu. Will be back!

(Translated by Google) Rich food but many things are missing. There is no ketchup or barbecue. Nor diet coke.  (Original) Rica comida pero faltan muchas cosas. No hay ketchup ni barbacoa. Tampoco diet coke.
nice dishes, also delivers, just small portions
Delicious tongue titillating food. If you're a foodie you'll love this place.

Solid, but not to crave, feels expensive for some dishes (chips/guac). Margarita good. Special roti with marrow rich and tasty. Cobia tacos well cooked and prepared. Tortillas and guacamole, standard. Lamb in Coca-Cola, very strong flavor in the glaze, lost the lamb flavor.
They get food right (i.e. it tastes great) and best of all, they somehow keep the volume down so groups can actually talk to one another. A rarity on BK. Also, great cocktails.
Delectable brunch, breakfast quesadilla was delish, excellent service
Pretty good food, pretty good ambiance
Awesome spot. Good prices and individual french press coffee. Food was tasty.
Best burger ever! Service was excellent!

This place is legit. Probably one of my favorite restaurants in Brooklyn at the moment. Their cocktails are tasty and creative, their food strikes a balance between authenticity and innovation that is sometimes hard to achieve with Mexican cuisine. The owners are also really nice.
Very delicious brunch. French press coffee and smaller portions - more of an upscale feel than Chavela's. No wait at noon on a Sunday.
Good food and best bartender megane
So much yum.
Amazing food, drinks, and service! Will definitely be back!
Amazing flavors! Loved every we ordered. Our favorites are shrimps tacos and coca cola ribs
Amazing rainbow of flavors.

(Translated by Google) Definitely a place to enjoy good food. The staff and the atmosphere stand out. If I go back to NYC it will be a must see.  (Original) Definitivamente un lugar para disfrutar de buena comida. El personal y el ambiente destacan. Si vuelvo a NYC será visita obligada.

(Translated by Google) Authentic Mexican touch in their meals, dishes are creative and sophisticated, we will definitely return. 100% recommended! 😄  (Original) Auténtico toque mexicano en sus comidas, platos son creativos y sofisticados, sin duda volveremos. 100% recomendado! 😄

The name says it all. High quality and highly creative dishes. Nothing we didn't like. Shrimp tacos to die for, as is rice dish with octopus and pork belly. Highly recommended. We'll definitely be back.

My wife and I absolutely love this restaurant! We've been several times since it's opened, the cocktails are excellent and the food is out of this world. The tacos and the coca-cola lamb are our personal favorites. Also highly recommend their happy hour, the homemade chips and salsa are delicious and there's a great selection of margaritas available too.
Chilaquiles were amazing.

I was pleasantly surprised by the Huevos Benedict, both the taste and my fullness. When my plate came, I thought it was not enough to fill me. So my friend and I ordered a side of Papa Braves. At the end we struggled to finish our food. My dish tasted like a juicy burrito with the eggs. My friend's Chilaquiles & Fideos was rich and creamy, but I preferred mine. The table next to us ordered a Breakfast Quesadilla that looked delicious. Will definitely give that one a try next time.  Huevos Benedict $12 Chilaquiles & Fideos $9
Fantastic creative Mexican
Outstanding service, great vibe.  Food is excellent, creative, thoughtful.  Drinks are delicious! Definitely going back!
My husband and I had a spectacular dinner here. Truly, the food—and drinks—knocked our socks off. We will most certainly be back. Often. Too many highlights to list, but don't miss the ceviche.

I am glad I waited for this place to open! I went and I will be returning. The food was spectacular. The flavors that you experience here will blow your mind it really is a must try! Definitely get the shrimp tempura taco and guacamole and tortilla!
Exceptionally well prepared food
Found this gem by mistake, the next will be on purpose 💓
All I can say is AMAZING!

One of the best Mexican restaurants ever! Their food is extremely good and creative, flavors are rich (although not as spicy as in Mexico), and their service is impeccable. They don't take phone reservations, but you are always welcome to walk in and wait at the bar.  PS I loved their Cinco de Mayo specials! Mexican cheese fondue was awesome 🧀 !
We had the huevos divociados and the huevos rancheros, both were awesome! Great Mexican brunch & great vibe. Mmmm
I can't speak highly enough of this place - every dish was superb. Get the coca-cola lamb ribs!
Absolutely delicious & sophisticated Mexican-style food & drinks. Lovely ambiance. Great addition to Vanderbilt.
Some of the best food I've ever had in Brooklyn! Insanely good food with awesome drinks. Get the squid and pork with the Trotters dish!

Had 3 dishes, they were all outstanding.  Lovely well designed spot with great jams in the bathroom that make you want to dance for a second before you go back to the bar.  Good service and nice cocktails.  Yes please!
Good!!
Just what this neighborhood was in need of.  Superb food, gracious staff and a perfectly appointed space.  I'll be here A LOT!

Brand new Latin inspired dinner spot. Food is fresh, uncluttered, and has a lot of flavor. Individual dishes are a little small, but the shared dishes are great. Still working out the menu, but a welcome high-end addition to the neighborhood.

This place was so, so good. We'd met the owner and the bartender last week as they were setting up the restaurant, and we couldn't wait to come once they opened. David, the bartender, was so helpful giving recommendations of what to get on the menu (although, from what we experienced, you can't really go wrong). We had an awesome meal, loved the ambiance, and cannot wait to go again. They'll have a liquor license any day now, and apparently have a slew of tequila-sounding drinks on the way. Very fun! Great addition to the neighborhood.
Great addition to the neighborhood. Queso simple and pork belly octopus were amazing.
